mbines detailed biographies of the artists with an examination of their work. This book will appeal to those interested in art as well as to art historians, urban historians, women's studies specialists, and policy makers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077356473240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773564732423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773564732/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles